commitmsg: rendering of search results is now done server side.

rewored how views are manipulated

added the detail format

printing the pk infront of the object for easy access during update/delete
records now are printed like they would apear in a bind file.

working on search. Ending here for tonight.
time: 2hr
dispatch is where all the work happens.
added some options and started on INTR records.
updated readme on how to update invtool

Merge branch 'master' of github.com:uberj/inv-tool

Conflicts:
	CHANGES.txt
add a new line after output and introduce the --pk-only flag
helper script to reset ldap password

Added SYS api and CSV commands

* The SYS api now supports creating, updating, and deleting system objects
* A new top level command lets you use the Inventory Search language to filter system objects and emit them in CSV format
* Minor refactoring was done to lib/options.py and lib/dns_options.py

Added invtool.kv to packages.

If you were exporting your PYTHONPATH this would not have effected you.
added KV crud support for VLAN/NET/SITE objects
rest api for networks vlans and sites
refactored kv stuff and added ro interface to network/site objects
let env resolve which python we get. fixes #3

Make auth lazy.

This makes it possible to run stuff like --help without entering
credentials.

Merge pull request #4 from bhearsum/username-prompt

Prompt for username/password when not in config file.
Prompt for username/password when not in config file.
fixed up the install doc a bit and appended keychain to requirements.txt

update keyring support

1. Try to use the keychain
2. Try to use the plain text
3. Try to configure the keychain
4. Fail and tell the user to configure the keychain or set a plain text password

Man page is comming along nicely
added comment option and changed some return values
return 1 when no results are returned from a search
no more label and domain options
instead of --format json and --format silent, you should now do --json or --silent
no more printing! all messages are bubbled up to the calling function. --silent works now.
